WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:01:04.272 --> 00:01:06.883
So they're still waiting at the ER?

00:01:09.897 --> 00:01:12.539
No, you don't have to. I'll call again later.

00:01:12.539 --> 00:01:14.556
Just let me out here.

00:01:14.556 --> 00:01:16.797
You're still pretty far. Just past the intersection...

00:01:16.797 --> 00:01:19.522
In Ah... In Ah!

00:02:37.231 --> 00:02:39.167
Excuse me, hold on a second.

00:02:39.167 --> 00:02:40.961
Wasn't surgery supposed to start right away?

00:02:40.961 --> 00:02:42.170
What's the holdup here?

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:45.090
Hold on a moment, please.

00:02:47.022 --> 00:02:48.958
Is our OR still not ready?

00:02:48.958 --> 00:02:51.732
Everything's full. The last one got taken by a VIP case.

00:02:51.732 --> 00:02:52.764
What is it?

00:02:52.764 --> 00:02:56.139
What about a switch or backup team, then?

00:02:56.139 --> 00:02:59.955
You can't just leave him like that. Do something!

00:03:00.772 --> 00:03:02.540
In Ah.

00:03:03.432 --> 00:03:05.151
You can pull strings, right?

00:03:05.151 --> 00:03:06.903
Make a call to Haemu Hospital, please?

00:03:06.903 --> 00:03:10.157
Please, I'm begging you. Help me out?

00:03:14.035 --> 00:03:16.329
[Surgery Time]

00:03:16.329 --> 00:03:18.182
[Surgery Time, Current Time, Anesthesia Time]

00:03:31.855 --> 00:03:36.433
Rest easy. Professor Yoon is the top trauma surgeon around.

00:03:36.433 --> 00:03:38.935
I'll be watching this through till the end.

00:03:38.935 --> 00:03:40.228
Thank you, Director.

00:03:40.228 --> 00:03:41.996
I'll be off.

00:03:48.778 --> 00:03:51.475
[Operating Room]

00:05:22.939 --> 00:05:25.272
Are you awake?

00:05:25.272 --> 00:05:27.101
Hey.

00:05:54.195 --> 00:05:57.834
[Episode 8: Wanting and Resenting]

00:05:59.909 --> 00:06:02.397
Catch me if you can.

00:06:08.314 --> 00:06:10.795
What is this, a kids' playground?

00:06:10.795 --> 00:06:13.256
Hello, patient here.

00:06:13.256 --> 00:06:16.618
Just let me rest, please, okay?

00:06:16.618 --> 00:06:19.598
Hey, we splurged on this for you, and you won't even eat?

00:06:19.598 --> 00:06:22.939
Forget it. Nothing tastes good right now. You three finish it.

00:06:22.939 --> 00:06:25.936
Oh, poor baby, no appetite?

00:06:25.936 --> 00:06:27.098
Tell me if anything sounds good.

00:06:27.098 --> 00:06:28.771
I'll make it for you on the spot.

00:06:28.771 --> 00:06:30.231
Hey, by the way, lately...

00:06:30.231 --> 00:06:32.109
That woman hasn't shown up?

00:06:33.026 --> 00:06:34.437
You know, Ms. Joo!

00:06:34.437 --> 00:06:35.528
Right?

00:06:35.528 --> 00:06:38.105
She was here all the time when you were knocked out.

00:06:38.105 --> 00:06:41.076
Staring at you with this tender look.

00:06:41.076 --> 00:06:43.829
But now that you're awake, not once?

00:06:43.829 --> 00:06:48.141
Maybe his energy comes back when she shows up?

00:06:48.141 --> 00:06:50.956
Your consciousness came back while she was here, remember?

00:06:52.003 --> 00:06:53.861
What's going on between you two?

00:06:53.861 --> 00:06:56.041
Doesn't look like just a coworker thing.

00:06:56.041 --> 00:06:58.593
Something's up, right?

00:06:58.593 --> 00:07:02.738
Are you guys more than just boss and employee?

00:07:04.481 --> 00:07:08.103
Drop it already. Seriously, please.

00:07:08.103 --> 00:07:10.839
Are you getting shy?

00:07:10.839 --> 00:07:14.860
Look at you, so cute.

00:07:14.860 --> 00:07:16.529
Quit it. Come on.

00:08:05.410 --> 00:08:07.107
Smells amazing.

00:08:18.356 --> 00:08:20.883
What is this? Am I your trained puppy?

00:08:20.883 --> 00:08:22.885
Toast delivery at the crack of dawn?

00:08:22.885 --> 00:08:25.179
Hey, you still came, though.

00:08:25.179 --> 00:08:26.762
Fear brought me here, fear.

00:08:26.762 --> 00:08:29.153
Who sends twenty-plus texts for one piece of toast?

00:08:29.153 --> 00:08:30.226
Well, then...

00:08:30.226 --> 00:08:32.481
What scared you so much when I was still out cold?

00:08:32.481 --> 00:08:34.897
Coming by day and night every single day.

00:08:34.897 --> 00:08:37.256
Taking such devoted care of me?

00:08:39.122 --> 00:08:41.613
My sisters spilled everything.

00:08:41.613 --> 00:08:44.334
Said it was heartbreaking to watch from the side.

00:08:47.022 --> 00:08:48.654
Fear, yeah.

00:08:51.064 --> 00:08:52.599
It really got to me.

00:08:54.814 --> 00:08:58.105
And as your superior...

00:08:58.105 --> 00:09:00.465
Protecting my staff means checking the status.

00:09:00.465 --> 00:09:02.692
Dead or alive, you know.

00:09:14.314 --> 00:09:18.910
Right, purely staff protection.

00:09:18.910 --> 00:09:21.929
While you're at it with the staff protection...

00:09:21.929 --> 00:09:24.546
Discharge me too, why don't you?

00:09:25.490 --> 00:09:26.923
Me?

00:09:26.923 --> 00:09:28.222
Yeah.

00:09:34.665 --> 00:09:36.897
Easy, easy with that.

00:09:36.897 --> 00:09:38.962
Lots of breakables in there.

00:09:38.962 --> 00:09:42.439
Stuck in one hospital room and somehow your stuff multiplied?

00:09:42.439 --> 00:09:45.734
Turns out deliveries reach the room just fine.

00:09:49.890 --> 00:09:52.484
What in the world am I even doing right now?

00:09:53.351 --> 00:09:56.381
Why's discharging you falling on me?

00:09:56.381 --> 00:09:58.356
The stitches in my abs haven't come out yet.

00:09:58.356 --> 00:10:01.481
This stuff is heavy, and nobody else is picking me up.

00:10:01.481 --> 00:10:04.837
Isn't this exactly when staff protection kicks in?

00:10:06.656 --> 00:10:07.907
Just you wait.

00:10:07.907 --> 00:10:09.231
The second those stitches come out...

00:10:09.231 --> 00:10:10.785
your labor is mine.

00:10:10.785 --> 00:10:13.272
I'll squeeze every last drop out of you.

00:10:13.272 --> 00:10:14.872
Got it.

00:10:14.872 --> 00:10:16.750
See, that's what I'm saying.

00:10:16.750 --> 00:10:19.669
That whole area is seriously undervalued right now.

00:10:19.669 --> 00:10:21.838
People might say it's old development talk.

00:10:21.838 --> 00:10:23.855
But land never lets you down.

00:10:23.855 --> 00:10:25.855
Sure thing.

00:10:25.855 --> 00:10:28.553
<i>You can't just leave him like that. Do something!</i>

00:10:28.553 --> 00:10:31.225
<i>Please, I'm begging you. Help me out?</i>

00:10:34.688 --> 00:10:36.153
Right, brother?

00:10:37.772 --> 00:10:39.455
We'll see.

00:10:40.558 --> 00:10:43.568
Anyway, this guy always misses the timing.

00:10:43.568 --> 00:10:47.447
He isn't keen on tearing that place down.

00:10:47.447 --> 00:10:50.661
Lots of folks would lose their livelihoods, I suppose.

00:10:50.661 --> 00:10:52.228
Compensation's on the table.

00:10:52.228 --> 00:10:54.157
Nobody's just kicking people out.

00:10:54.157 --> 00:10:57.833
Yeah well, my big brother's got a soft heart.

00:10:57.833 --> 00:11:00.877
Since we were kids, he couldn't walk past anyone struggling.

00:11:00.877 --> 00:11:04.172
Always giving in, sacrificing.

00:11:04.172 --> 00:11:06.558
Our family's been tough for generations... you know my old man, right?

00:11:06.558 --> 00:11:09.401
The fiercest man in all of Korea.

00:11:11.096 --> 00:11:13.917
Beats me who my brother takes after.

00:11:13.917 --> 00:11:15.809
One thing's certain.

00:11:15.809 --> 00:11:17.786
It isn't Dad's side.

00:11:19.022 --> 00:11:21.622
Has to be Mom's, definitely Mom's.

00:11:41.231 --> 00:11:42.772
Sorry about that.

00:11:42.772 --> 00:11:43.772
I'll apologize for him.

00:11:43.772 --> 00:11:45.896
He's had way too much to drink.

00:11:46.814 --> 00:11:49.022
PR's been contacted. Get the car ready.

00:11:49.022 --> 00:11:51.443
I'll bring him down right now.

00:12:04.064 --> 00:12:06.160
Ah Jeong, you made it.

00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:08.377
Why are you acting out of character?

00:12:09.908 --> 00:12:13.246
The board meeting is right around the corner. How can you be this reckless?

00:12:14.481 --> 00:12:16.790
Cut me some slack today.

00:12:25.272 --> 00:12:26.829
Joo In Ah.

00:12:27.469 --> 00:12:30.858
What exactly is that woman to you?

00:12:32.719 --> 00:12:35.654
The woman I'd die alongside.

00:12:42.700 --> 00:12:46.126
Seriously, not one emergency umbrella in this car?

00:12:46.855 --> 00:12:50.377
I'll have to stash one in here next time.

00:12:52.948 --> 00:12:56.534
If Ah Jeong's home, why not ask her to bring an umbrella?

00:12:56.534 --> 00:12:58.921
No need to go that far...

00:12:58.921 --> 00:13:02.097
Looks like a quick shower. I'll just sit it out.

00:13:06.688 --> 00:13:09.022
So why did things end with Ah Jeong?

00:13:09.756 --> 00:13:11.228
The reason's a mystery to me, too.

00:13:11.228 --> 00:13:13.564
She just up and ghosted me one day.

00:13:13.564 --> 00:13:15.177
Didn't you ask her why?

00:13:15.177 --> 00:13:17.105
You must have run into her at work.

00:13:17.105 --> 00:13:18.697
Never asked.

00:13:19.557 --> 00:13:21.861
She kept quiet for a reason.

00:13:26.439 --> 00:13:27.712
What?

00:13:28.358 --> 00:13:32.142
Would you have pressed her till the end?

00:13:34.231 --> 00:13:36.439
If it were me...

00:13:36.439 --> 00:13:38.728
If I were in Ah Jeong's shoes...

00:13:40.221 --> 00:13:42.368
That's probably what I'd have wanted.

00:13:45.333 --> 00:13:48.253
There's this weird thing where at crucial moments...

00:13:48.253 --> 00:13:50.439
I end up hiding what I really feel.

00:13:51.408 --> 00:13:53.478
And at the same time...

00:13:54.105 --> 00:13:57.261
Part of me wishes someone would drag me out of it.

00:13:57.261 --> 00:14:00.474
Refuse to give up on me no matter what.

00:14:00.474 --> 00:14:03.617
A selfish, contradictory feeling like that creeps in.

00:14:06.231 --> 00:14:10.541
Why not just lay it all out honestly then?

00:14:13.730 --> 00:14:15.446
<i>Are you serious?</i>

00:14:15.446 --> 00:14:18.249
<i>So I should go through with this marriage?</i>

00:14:18.249 --> 00:14:19.769
<i>Yeah, dead serious.</i>

00:14:19.769 --> 00:14:22.681
<i>What's the alternative, run away together?</i>

00:14:22.681 --> 00:14:25.915
<i>Kicked out of home, stripped of everything?</i>

00:14:25.915 --> 00:14:27.549
<i>That's not the life I want.</i>

00:14:27.549 --> 00:14:30.175
<i>- In Ah. - And besides...</i>

00:14:30.175 --> 00:14:33.564
<i>Naive thoughts about us lasting forever?</i>

00:14:33.564 --> 00:14:35.688
<i>Never crossed my mind, not even once.</i>

00:14:35.688 --> 00:14:38.804
<i>So drop the guilt and walk away with a clear head.</i>

00:14:38.804 --> 00:14:40.931
<i>Honestly, I'm...</i>

00:14:40.931 --> 00:14:42.948
<i>Truly fine.</i>

00:14:49.523 --> 00:14:51.104
Probably...

00:14:51.104 --> 00:14:54.283
The truth is I don't know how to be happy.

00:14:58.314 --> 00:15:01.887
The moment something feels like happiness, anxiety creeps in.

00:15:01.887 --> 00:15:04.772
Am I really someone who deserves this?

00:15:04.772 --> 00:15:06.373
Fear takes over.

00:15:06.373 --> 00:15:08.490
And I hide, retreat.

00:15:09.667 --> 00:15:12.270
Misery feels safe and cozy, after all.

00:15:19.105 --> 00:15:20.692
Close your eyes.

00:15:21.471 --> 00:15:23.445
Why?

00:15:23.445 --> 00:15:26.769
Nothing weird, I promise. Just close them.

00:15:30.189 --> 00:15:31.440
There.

00:15:32.431 --> 00:15:34.499
What do you hear?

00:15:35.105 --> 00:15:36.653
Rain, obviously.

00:15:36.653 --> 00:15:39.980
Calm down and really focus on it, alright?

00:15:54.081 --> 00:15:57.465
Raindrops hitting the windshield.

00:15:57.465 --> 00:15:59.439
And?

00:15:59.439 --> 00:16:00.785
And?

00:16:01.886 --> 00:16:03.220
The car engine running.

00:16:03.220 --> 00:16:04.481
And?

00:16:07.481 --> 00:16:10.028
A motorcycle going by outside.

00:16:11.050 --> 00:16:12.418
And?

00:16:17.105 --> 00:16:18.582
Kids...

00:16:19.236 --> 00:16:20.918
laughing in the distance.

00:16:21.630 --> 00:16:22.934
And?

00:16:25.993 --> 00:16:28.287
Your breathing.

00:16:28.287 --> 00:16:29.582
And?

00:16:35.064 --> 00:16:36.957
My heart beating.

00:16:42.022 --> 00:16:44.486
That's how you feel it.

00:16:46.680 --> 00:16:48.363
Happiness,

00:16:48.363 --> 00:16:50.726
when you pour your whole heart into it.

00:16:50.726 --> 00:16:53.245
And look quietly inside.

00:16:54.523 --> 00:16:57.609
It's right there inside you, for sure.

00:16:57.609 --> 00:17:00.028
It's always sitting there.

00:17:00.028 --> 00:17:01.968
Whenever you want to find it,

00:17:03.688 --> 00:17:05.788
find it just like this.

00:17:37.398 --> 00:17:39.189
Glad to have you back.

00:17:39.189 --> 00:17:40.401
You've been through a lot.

00:17:40.401 --> 00:17:42.653
Thank you.

00:17:42.653 --> 00:17:44.616
You went through a lot.

00:17:44.616 --> 00:17:46.574
But your face is

00:17:46.574 --> 00:17:47.993
looking better.

00:17:47.993 --> 00:17:50.189
Hospital food must have agreed with you.

00:17:50.189 --> 00:17:52.788
Skipping the office does wonders for the complexion, doesn't it?

00:17:52.788 --> 00:17:54.540
Oh, come on now.

00:17:54.540 --> 00:17:57.043
His face was always sharp to begin with.

00:17:57.043 --> 00:17:59.745
The whole Audit Office lit up with you back.

00:17:59.745 --> 00:18:01.564
Glad to have you back.

00:18:01.564 --> 00:18:05.051
I really missed you so much.

00:18:05.051 --> 00:18:07.137
Tone it down, way too much.

00:18:07.137 --> 00:18:09.330
Don't worry about Mr. Ahn one bit.

00:18:09.330 --> 00:18:12.221
Legal is hammering away at this right now.

00:18:12.221 --> 00:18:13.592
He's going down hard, count on it.

00:18:13.592 --> 00:18:15.955
Word is, even his family cut him loose.

00:18:15.955 --> 00:18:17.063
Reaping what he sowed, plain and simple.

00:18:17.063 --> 00:18:18.480
You've been through a lot.

00:18:18.480 --> 00:18:19.494
Yes.

00:18:19.494 --> 00:18:21.650
Hey, Team 3 sure adores you.

00:18:21.650 --> 00:18:24.028
Boy, were you ever against going at first.

00:18:24.028 --> 00:18:25.268
No, you were dying to go.

00:18:25.268 --> 00:18:27.010
Yeah, totally itching for it.

00:18:27.010 --> 00:18:29.534
Yeah, that's right.

00:18:29.534 --> 00:18:31.522
Good day, Ms. Joo.

00:18:33.579 --> 00:18:35.573
Good to have you back.

00:18:35.573 --> 00:18:37.082
Yes. Good to be back.

00:18:37.082 --> 00:18:39.793
Do you have any plans for today?

00:18:39.793 --> 00:18:43.146
Almost didn't recognize you. You're glowing more than usual.

00:18:46.384 --> 00:18:49.596
What, was I gloomy before or something?

00:18:49.596 --> 00:18:51.847
No, that's not what I meant...

00:18:51.847 --> 00:18:53.933
Something good must be in the air, huh?

00:18:53.933 --> 00:18:56.311
Like a favorite staff member's comeback maybe?

00:18:56.311 --> 00:18:59.143
- Such a warm welcome rolled out for me... - Mr. Noh.

00:19:01.272 --> 00:19:05.198
Looks like a long absence dulled your office instincts.

00:19:09.288 --> 00:19:11.776
Better whip those back into shape fast.

00:19:18.458 --> 00:19:21.043
She still can't stand you, it seems.

00:19:21.043 --> 00:19:24.756
All that fighting through the injury for nothing, sad.

00:19:28.314 --> 00:19:29.855
Hey, no problem.

00:19:29.855 --> 00:19:31.720
This much is nothing.

00:19:31.720 --> 00:19:34.897
Noh Ki Jun, Audit Office ace right here.

00:19:34.897 --> 00:19:36.605
Thanks.

00:19:36.605 --> 00:19:38.994
All right, let's do this.

00:20:03.545 --> 00:20:07.339
<i>Every assignment you handed over is done.</i>

00:20:07.339 --> 00:20:08.674
[Audit Office, Head Joo In Ah]

00:20:08.674 --> 00:20:09.854
[Okey-dokey]

00:20:11.206 --> 00:20:13.653
Okey-dokey?

00:20:17.184 --> 00:20:19.397
That's harsh.

00:20:22.856 --> 00:20:26.335
[That's harsh] First day back from being sick and...

00:20:29.439 --> 00:20:32.073
<i>Hard work earns a meal. I'll treat you.</i>

00:20:32.073 --> 00:20:33.118
<i>For real?</i>

00:20:33.118 --> 00:20:34.700
<i>When?</i>

00:20:34.700 --> 00:20:37.118
[Audit Office, Head Joo In Ah]

00:20:49.716 --> 00:20:53.067
<i>Friday evening. Come to my place.</i>

00:20:58.391 --> 00:21:00.110
What's wrong?

00:21:02.523 --> 00:21:05.372
My back is killing me.

00:21:27.814 --> 00:21:29.587
Mr. Noh.

00:21:29.587 --> 00:21:31.508
Hey, Doo Gi.

00:21:31.508 --> 00:21:35.220
Sorry I never made it to visit while you were laid up.

00:21:35.220 --> 00:21:37.078
No big deal.

00:21:37.078 --> 00:21:38.639
If you took a stab wound...

00:21:38.639 --> 00:21:41.897
visiting wouldn't be on my list either, so we're even.

00:21:41.897 --> 00:21:44.119
Come on, that's harsh.

00:21:45.145 --> 00:21:46.479
By the way...

00:21:46.479 --> 00:21:49.250
Got a work thing I wanted to run by you.

00:21:49.898 --> 00:21:51.919
Haemu Pharma was your last beat, right?

00:21:51.919 --> 00:21:53.118
Yeah, it was.

00:21:53.118 --> 00:21:56.605
Anything in particular you were digging into back then?

00:21:56.605 --> 00:21:58.356
What are you talking about?

00:21:58.356 --> 00:21:59.494
The handover was complete.

00:21:59.494 --> 00:22:01.594
Didn't you check the cloud folder?

00:22:02.412 --> 00:22:03.462
Yeah.

00:22:03.462 --> 00:22:05.542
Nothing in there caught my eye.

00:22:05.542 --> 00:22:06.773
Empty?

00:22:06.773 --> 00:22:08.435
Right.

00:22:10.405 --> 00:22:12.274
Let me look into it and circle back.

00:22:12.274 --> 00:22:14.232
- Got it. - Right.

00:22:22.798 --> 00:22:25.555
<i>A subsidiary audit case was sitting on my desk, a big one.</i>

00:22:25.555 --> 00:22:26.959
<i>Let me see it through to the end.</i>

00:22:26.959 --> 00:22:29.167
<i>Get the files squared away on the department cloud.</i>

00:22:29.167 --> 00:22:31.624
<i>Once that's done, I'll review and handle the handover.</i>

00:22:35.404 --> 00:22:38.699
[Handover]

00:22:38.699 --> 00:22:40.859
[No search results were found for files and folders related to Noh Ki Jun Handover]

00:22:50.231 --> 00:22:52.671
Jae Hong, you slammed right now?

00:22:52.671 --> 00:22:54.688
Listen, I need a favor.

00:22:54.688 --> 00:22:58.818
A file I uploaded to the department cloud just vanished into thin air.

00:23:07.397 --> 00:23:10.288
Oh, perfect.

00:23:20.397 --> 00:23:22.137
What can I get you?

00:23:22.137 --> 00:23:25.496
For someone bouncing back from being sick...

00:23:25.496 --> 00:23:27.497
what dish helps with the recovery?

00:23:27.497 --> 00:23:28.622
Korean beef is the way.

00:23:28.622 --> 00:23:30.861
What's on the menu?

00:23:30.861 --> 00:23:33.814
Something easy that looks impressive...

00:23:33.814 --> 00:23:37.538
simple but with a sophisticated touch?

00:23:37.538 --> 00:23:40.298
Just pack up everything on display here.

00:23:40.298 --> 00:23:42.688
- All of it? - Practice runs are part of the plan.

00:23:42.688 --> 00:23:44.447
Got it.

00:23:53.732 --> 00:23:56.968
<i>That folder was deleted two days later.</i>

00:23:56.968 --> 00:23:59.254
The trace points to Joo In Ah's PC.

00:24:14.253 --> 00:24:17.807
[Haemu Pharma]

00:24:19.716 --> 00:24:22.435
[Requires Review: Haemu Pharma]

00:24:33.147 --> 00:24:35.190
<i>Whole garlic cloves, here we go.</i>

00:24:35.190 --> 00:24:37.564
<i>These are getting sliced in half too.</i>

00:24:37.564 --> 00:24:40.320
<i>Slicing them too thin kills the flavor.</i>

00:24:40.320 --> 00:24:43.615
<i>Keep them chunky and pile on the garlic.</i>

00:24:43.615 --> 00:24:47.662
<i>Eating it that way is good for your health on top of it.</i>

00:24:57.147 --> 00:24:58.672
<i>Set the wok on the table.</i>

00:24:58.672 --> 00:25:02.855
<i>- A few drops of sesame oil will do.</i> - Oil first...

00:25:02.855 --> 00:25:06.147
<i>- One spoon of garlic going in.</i> - Oil...

00:25:06.147 --> 00:25:08.865
Oil's missing here, oil...

00:26:04.772 --> 00:26:07.840
This tastes incredible, oh my.

00:26:18.996 --> 00:26:20.375
Hey.

00:26:21.403 --> 00:26:23.313
In this early?

00:26:24.174 --> 00:26:26.308
Or did you skip going home altogether?

00:26:32.481 --> 00:26:35.667
What's going on?

00:26:39.730 --> 00:26:41.917
Back on your very first day here,

00:26:44.055 --> 00:26:46.948
what was the real reason you pushed me to Team 3?

00:26:54.512 --> 00:26:57.833
Still bitter about the PM assignment?

00:26:57.833 --> 00:27:01.420
PM work, by my read, is no small matter.

00:27:01.420 --> 00:27:03.431
You've done it firsthand, so the weight of it must've registered.

00:27:03.431 --> 00:27:07.302
How much the private bleeds into the professional.

00:27:07.302 --> 00:27:10.109
Emotions are tangled in, which makes handling it tricky.

00:27:10.707 --> 00:27:12.766
Someone like you,

00:27:12.766 --> 00:27:17.375
with that confidence and sharpness of yours, untouched by what others think,

00:27:17.375 --> 00:27:18.828
the call was that you'd pull it off.

00:27:18.828 --> 00:27:20.441
Turned out the call was right.

00:27:25.814 --> 00:27:27.814
That's the whole of it?

00:27:27.814 --> 00:27:29.340
Any other reason?

00:27:31.022 --> 00:27:32.699
Nothing else, truly?

00:27:40.333 --> 00:27:42.022
[Special Audit Report on Sponsorships and Governance of J Care Foundation]

00:27:42.022 --> 00:27:44.147
J Care Foundation.

00:27:44.147 --> 00:27:48.135
Haemu Pharma backs this medical entity under their CSR initiative.

00:27:48.135 --> 00:27:49.718
On its face, nothing wrong there.

00:27:49.718 --> 00:27:52.554
Funding hits the place generously, though.

00:27:52.554 --> 00:27:56.066
A legal entity with zero name recognition, zero track record.

00:28:00.311 --> 00:28:02.356
So I dug.

00:28:02.356 --> 00:28:05.984
Followed the trail, layer after layer, doggedly all the way down.

00:28:05.984 --> 00:28:09.957
[J Care Foundation]

00:28:09.957 --> 00:28:12.408
The structure was twisted into knots, ridiculously so.

00:28:12.408 --> 00:28:13.479
[J Care Foundation]

00:28:14.553 --> 00:28:17.487
At the end of the line, the real owner of this entity is...

00:28:20.916 --> 00:28:23.323
Vice Chairman Jeon Jae Yeol.

00:28:23.323 --> 00:28:25.712
This entity,

00:28:25.712 --> 00:28:28.430
Vice Chairman Jeon Jae Yeol founded it, didn't he?

00:28:35.284 --> 00:28:37.225
The floor is yours now.

00:28:37.225 --> 00:28:39.186
Is there a connection?

00:28:39.186 --> 00:28:42.790
Between this and the reason I had to be moved to Team 3.

00:28:46.064 --> 00:28:47.150
<i>Alright.</i>

00:28:47.150 --> 00:28:49.794
<i>Your position needs adjusting.</i>

00:28:53.782 --> 00:28:57.037
[Noh Ki Jun Audit Team 1 Handover]

00:28:57.037 --> 00:28:58.267
[Permanent Deletion]

00:29:00.997 --> 00:29:03.458
[Delete Noh Ki Jun Audit Team 1 Handover and all subfolders for good?]

00:29:03.458 --> 00:29:06.142
[Noh Ki Jun Audit Team 1 Handover file has been permanently deleted]

00:29:08.423 --> 00:29:11.023
Pulling the plug on the investigation, yes, that was me.

00:29:13.220 --> 00:29:16.096
But the Vice Chairman pocketing personal gain,

00:29:16.096 --> 00:29:18.034
or anything off in Haemu Pharma's internal process,

00:29:18.034 --> 00:29:19.528
my read was that none of it held up.

00:29:19.528 --> 00:29:21.272
But that kind of...

00:29:21.272 --> 00:29:24.514
judgment call shouldn't sit on your shoulders alone.

00:29:24.514 --> 00:29:29.189
Reporting up, putting it before the board, running a special investigation,

00:29:29.189 --> 00:29:30.819
isn't that the order of business here?

00:29:30.819 --> 00:29:33.365
The substance and the fallout would've blown out of proportion,

00:29:33.365 --> 00:29:36.466
- with everyone turning into political pawns... - The damage would've landed

00:29:36.466 --> 00:29:38.759
on Vice Chairman Jeon Jae Yeol.

00:29:44.419 --> 00:29:47.764
Did some kind of favor come your way from him?

00:29:48.545 --> 00:29:50.749
He has no clue I even know.

00:29:59.147 --> 00:30:00.939
A person as airtight as you

00:30:00.939 --> 00:30:02.642
with the line between work and personal drawn crystal clear,

00:30:02.642 --> 00:30:05.426
worried that Jeon Jae Yeol might take a hit,

00:30:05.426 --> 00:30:08.789
buried an issue like this by your own hand?

00:30:11.722 --> 00:30:15.030
Even if I drop it, the lid's coming off eventually, so...

00:30:15.030 --> 00:30:17.272
one way or the other,

00:30:17.272 --> 00:30:19.701
true to who you are,

00:30:19.701 --> 00:30:21.959
set the record straight, please.

00:30:28.756 --> 00:30:29.797
Mr. Noh.

00:30:29.797 --> 00:30:32.372
- In early today. - Good morning.

00:30:32.372 --> 00:30:34.732
- Good morning. - Good morning.

00:31:12.253 --> 00:31:13.965
This feels good.

00:31:13.965 --> 00:31:15.526
Refreshing.

00:31:23.814 --> 00:31:25.658
You're home?

00:31:27.688 --> 00:31:29.331
You're late today.

00:31:34.625 --> 00:31:37.857
Hey, have you been drinking?

00:32:26.189 --> 00:32:27.914
Yes, Chairperson,

00:32:27.914 --> 00:32:29.847
this is Joo In Ah.

00:32:31.376 --> 00:32:34.852
There's an additional item to be reported at tomorrow's board meeting.

00:32:38.564 --> 00:32:43.097
The final motion just passed as well.

00:32:46.897 --> 00:32:50.117
Head of Audit, would you like to speak?

00:32:50.871 --> 00:32:54.606
There's something the Audit Committee didn't get to earlier

00:32:54.606 --> 00:32:56.985
that I'd like to bring before the board now.

00:32:56.985 --> 00:32:59.404
Hold on for a second.

00:32:59.404 --> 00:33:03.005
Since this wasn't on the agenda in advance,

00:33:05.231 --> 00:33:08.624
Director Park Sang Hwan apparently has something to propose.

00:33:08.624 --> 00:33:09.915
The floor is yours.

00:33:09.915 --> 00:33:11.625
Yes.

00:33:11.625 --> 00:33:15.318
Please bear with me for raising this so abruptly.

00:33:16.586 --> 00:33:18.560
Due to health concerns,

00:33:18.560 --> 00:33:19.798
our Chairman

00:33:19.798 --> 00:33:23.185
is currently limited in carrying out official duties.

00:33:23.185 --> 00:33:26.763
As a result, a great deal of key executive decisions

00:33:26.763 --> 00:33:31.179
have been falling on Vice Chairman Jeon Jae Yeol alone.

00:33:31.179 --> 00:33:33.853
Yet the Chairman remains in good standing,

00:33:33.853 --> 00:33:36.815
and nothing has changed about him being our symbolic leader

00:33:36.815 --> 00:33:41.486
and the spiritual pillar of this group.

00:33:41.486 --> 00:33:43.015
With that in mind,

00:33:43.015 --> 00:33:45.740
to promote sharper decision-making

00:33:45.740 --> 00:33:49.007
and a more stable management environment,

00:33:50.439 --> 00:33:52.413
I'd like to put forward MD Jeon Seong Yeol

00:33:52.413 --> 00:33:56.741
for appointment as Co-Vice Chairman.

00:34:06.064 --> 00:34:08.523
What's wrong with Director Park?

00:34:08.523 --> 00:34:10.564
Wasn't he on the Vice Chairman's side?

00:34:10.564 --> 00:34:12.825
Looks like he flipped on him.

00:34:14.189 --> 00:34:16.287
Quiet down, everyone.

00:34:17.196 --> 00:34:20.814
We'll now move to a vote on the motion

00:34:20.814 --> 00:34:22.944
that Director Park has put forward.

00:34:22.944 --> 00:34:25.637
On the motion to appoint MD Jeon Seong Yeol

00:34:25.637 --> 00:34:28.116
as Co-Vice Chairman alongside Vice Chairman Jeon Jae Yeol,

00:34:28.116 --> 00:34:30.176
all directors in favor,

00:34:30.176 --> 00:34:32.678
please raise your hands.

00:35:22.314 --> 00:35:23.963
Director Park.

00:35:23.963 --> 00:35:26.356
I owe this to you. I truly appreciate it.

00:35:26.356 --> 00:35:28.567
Time for me to get in line, too.

00:35:37.894 --> 00:35:38.981
Congratulations, Vice Chairman.

00:35:38.981 --> 00:35:41.356
Right, Ms. Joo.

00:35:41.356 --> 00:35:45.735
That last-minute surprise threw me off, so it slipped my mind,

00:35:45.735 --> 00:35:48.201
but you mentioned you had something to report?

00:35:48.201 --> 00:35:51.462
Would you be submitting it in writing or anything like that?

00:35:51.462 --> 00:35:53.326
No, there's nothing.

00:35:53.326 --> 00:35:56.248
All right then.

00:36:04.688 --> 00:36:06.730
Congratulations.

00:36:06.730 --> 00:36:08.691
I owe this to you.

00:36:10.189 --> 00:36:13.231
I look forward to your continued guidance and support.

00:36:13.231 --> 00:36:15.223
The pleasure is all ours, sir...

00:36:15.223 --> 00:36:16.391
[This board meeting was wild]

00:36:16.391 --> 00:36:18.184
[Looks like Jeon Jae Yeol's people all jumped ship to the new Vice Chairman]

00:36:18.184 --> 00:36:19.227
No way.

00:36:19.227 --> 00:36:21.604
Does this mean we need sign-off from both Vice Chairmen now?

00:36:21.604 --> 00:36:24.232
Geez, who knows where this company is headed.

00:36:24.232 --> 00:36:26.903
Doesn't this make things pretty obvious?

00:36:26.903 --> 00:36:29.153
The smart move is hopping on the S side.

00:36:29.153 --> 00:36:31.614
So I caught wind of this from the executive secretaries,

00:36:31.614 --> 00:36:34.450
Director Park had been on the Vice Chairman's side from the start,

00:36:34.450 --> 00:36:37.122
but he turned on him this time around.

00:36:37.122 --> 00:36:39.812
Office politics are no joke.

00:36:39.812 --> 00:36:41.523
Hey, look how this turned out.

00:36:41.523 --> 00:36:43.251
What did? Who now?

00:36:43.251 --> 00:36:45.147
- Me? - Be honest with me.

00:36:45.147 --> 00:36:47.354
I'm on your side.

00:36:53.439 --> 00:36:56.405
Yes, that report is...

00:37:53.029 --> 00:37:55.828
[Assistant Manager Noh Ki Jun]

00:38:18.523 --> 00:38:21.509
<i>The number you've reached is unavailable. You'll be connected to voicemail</i>

00:38:21.509 --> 00:38:23.059
<i>after the tone, and standard rates apply...</i>

00:38:23.059 --> 00:38:24.999
[Joo In Ah]

00:39:02.557 --> 00:39:05.681
[Joo In Ah]

00:39:08.396 --> 00:39:11.220
[Joo In Ah]

00:40:05.870 --> 00:40:09.330
[Head of HR Bu Se Yeong]

00:40:13.002 --> 00:40:15.148
<i>Do you know what time it is?</i>

00:40:15.148 --> 00:40:16.642
Se Yeong.

00:40:17.605 --> 00:40:19.983
There's a favor I need from you.

00:40:23.523 --> 00:40:25.968
Hey, how can this be sprung on me like this?

00:40:25.968 --> 00:40:27.809
Wasn't my U.S. assignment put on hold?

00:40:27.809 --> 00:40:30.149
Right, that was just because you were out sick,

00:40:30.149 --> 00:40:31.788
so now that you're back on your feet, off you go.

00:40:31.788 --> 00:40:33.469
I'm not fully back to normal yet,

00:40:33.469 --> 00:40:34.849
and I've still got outpatient treatment to deal with.

00:40:34.849 --> 00:40:37.109
There are hospitals in the U.S. too, no need to worry.

00:40:37.109 --> 00:40:39.149
The company picks up all the medical bills.

00:40:39.149 --> 00:40:41.116
How great is that?

00:40:41.116 --> 00:40:42.448
So, has Ms. Joo been told?

00:40:42.448 --> 00:40:44.341
About this sudden reassignment?

00:40:45.022 --> 00:40:46.621
What are you talking about?

00:40:46.621 --> 00:40:48.980
- She's the one who asked for it. - What?

00:40:48.980 --> 00:40:52.105
She wanted your U.S. assignment fast-tracked as much as possible,

00:40:52.105 --> 00:40:53.846
called me at the crack of dawn.

00:40:53.846 --> 00:40:55.855
In exchange, she wanted you promoted right away,

00:40:55.855 --> 00:40:59.759
placed at the top branch and the most comfortable team.

00:40:59.759 --> 00:41:01.464
Looks like In Ah...

00:41:02.481 --> 00:41:04.675
really does care about you.

00:41:15.356 --> 00:41:17.769
[1g Gold Bar Giveaway]

00:41:25.840 --> 00:41:29.340
So everything up to this point was already cleared in the last audit?

00:41:29.340 --> 00:41:31.939
Yes, and since there was a major restructuring this time,

00:41:31.939 --> 00:41:33.701
I pulled up a brand-new sheet.

00:41:33.701 --> 00:41:36.393
I need a word with you.

00:41:37.253 --> 00:41:38.794
Can't you see I'm in the middle of a briefing?

00:41:38.794 --> 00:41:41.351
I said let's talk, right this minute!

00:41:47.513 --> 00:41:50.534
What's with this behavior?

00:41:52.562 --> 00:41:54.948
Hold off until Mr. Ahn is done.

00:42:05.973 --> 00:42:07.640
What did you want to say?

00:42:07.640 --> 00:42:09.320
Are you really asking like you don't know?

00:42:09.320 --> 00:42:11.360
What's going on with the U.S. assignment?

00:42:12.439 --> 00:42:14.753
Wasn't it already set for you to go?

00:42:14.753 --> 00:42:16.459
It's a great opportunity for you,

00:42:16.459 --> 00:42:18.630
and if you're heading there anyway, sooner is better.

00:42:18.630 --> 00:42:21.064
At the California branch, you'll get exposure to management work

00:42:21.064 --> 00:42:22.855
rather than just government relations.

00:42:22.855 --> 00:42:25.501
Forget all that. What's the real reason?

00:42:29.272 --> 00:42:30.688
Is this somehow...

00:42:31.939 --> 00:42:34.076
about J Care Foundation?

00:42:44.605 --> 00:42:47.632
I'm not such a clueless pushover that I can't get the picture.

00:42:47.632 --> 00:42:48.980
I was actually beating myself up,

00:42:48.980 --> 00:42:51.850
wondering if I pushed you too hard.

00:42:51.850 --> 00:42:54.980
I mean, when an old classmate you've barely heard from suddenly shows up

00:42:54.980 --> 00:42:57.544
asking for a single favor, it's hard to turn down.

00:42:57.544 --> 00:43:01.173
You might feel inclined to cover for an ex's slip-up.

00:43:01.173 --> 00:43:04.779
I regretted going overboard because of my feelings.

00:43:06.605 --> 00:43:08.287
No, you weren't overreacting.

00:43:10.855 --> 00:43:12.732
I don't think...

00:43:14.564 --> 00:43:16.662
I can promise to set things right.

00:43:25.356 --> 00:43:26.654
Why not?

00:43:27.428 --> 00:43:28.989
Worried Jeon Jae Yeol might take a hit?

00:43:28.989 --> 00:43:31.084
Does that weigh on you that much?

00:43:32.897 --> 00:43:34.943
Are you going back to him?

00:43:34.943 --> 00:43:36.814
Like the Little Prince

00:43:36.814 --> 00:43:40.530
heading back to his planet to see the rose he raised,

00:43:40.530 --> 00:43:43.465
is that what you're doing, going back to Jeon Jae Yeol?

00:43:45.189 --> 00:43:47.733
- No, that's not it at all. - Then...

00:43:48.637 --> 00:43:51.558
How on earth am I supposed to make sense of all of this?

00:43:51.558 --> 00:43:52.997
Is it my job...

00:43:55.980 --> 00:43:58.368
to make you understand?

00:44:01.397 --> 00:44:04.444
You'll be busy prepping for the assignment, so I'll pull you off duties for now.

00:44:04.444 --> 00:44:06.196
Get yourself ready.

00:44:07.486 --> 00:44:09.084
[Interview Room]

00:44:26.088 --> 00:44:27.103
Hey.

00:44:27.103 --> 00:44:28.544
Now that you're shipping off to the U.S.,

00:44:28.544 --> 00:44:30.344
you were really laying into Ms. Joo, weren't you?

00:44:30.344 --> 00:44:32.556
Right? My jaw nearly hit the floor.

00:44:32.556 --> 00:44:35.836
By the way, what were you two talking about earlier?

00:44:39.980 --> 00:44:42.271
Seriously, it's his own celebration,

00:44:42.271 --> 00:44:43.606
so why the long face?

00:44:43.606 --> 00:44:45.357
He's been doing nothing but downing shots.

00:44:45.357 --> 00:44:47.959
I know, right? On such a happy day.

00:44:48.647 --> 00:44:49.883
Oh come on, don't tell me

00:44:49.883 --> 00:44:52.284
you're sulking because you don't want to buy us drinks?

00:44:52.284 --> 00:44:53.916
Oh, no way.

00:44:56.994 --> 00:44:58.456
Sounds good.

00:44:58.456 --> 00:45:01.418
And for next week's Jeju business trip,

00:45:01.418 --> 00:45:04.525
Ms. Joo, you should join us as well.

00:45:04.525 --> 00:45:05.978
Me?

00:45:06.744 --> 00:45:08.659
What's there for the Audit Office to support...

00:45:08.659 --> 00:45:11.011
During your assignment, you worked on the CPK and JV deals.

00:45:11.011 --> 00:45:13.052
Bringing along a partner with experience

00:45:13.052 --> 00:45:15.564
would make the mood smoother.

00:45:15.564 --> 00:45:19.038
Then of course Ms. Joo has to be there.

00:45:19.038 --> 00:45:21.647
I'm jealous.

00:45:21.647 --> 00:45:24.454
Jeju must be amazing this time of year.

00:45:44.189 --> 00:45:46.560
<i>It's my birthday.</i>

00:45:49.049 --> 00:45:51.359
<i>How about giving it a try?</i>

00:45:55.639 --> 00:45:57.437
<i>What's this?</i>

00:46:16.824 --> 00:46:20.541
[Jeon Jae Yeol, Jeju]

00:46:33.939 --> 00:46:35.137
<i>Hello.</i>

00:46:35.137 --> 00:46:37.360
<i>Let's grab a drink. It's been ages.</i>

00:46:54.730 --> 00:46:57.007
You caught what was said in the meeting earlier, right?

00:46:57.007 --> 00:46:58.388
Get next week's trip in order.

00:46:58.388 --> 00:47:00.951
Why Joo In Ah, of all people?

00:47:00.951 --> 00:47:03.408
There's plenty of reason for her to come along.

00:47:03.408 --> 00:47:05.500
She's also acquainted with the experienced partner.

00:47:05.500 --> 00:47:07.677
Aside from that, the real reason.

00:47:08.987 --> 00:47:10.753
What are you trying to pull right now?

00:47:10.753 --> 00:47:13.330
What are you doing, Vice Chairman?

00:47:13.330 --> 00:47:14.730
You're picking fights while drunk,

00:47:14.730 --> 00:47:17.663
shipping off some employee overseas because of personal feelings.

00:47:17.663 --> 00:47:20.387
Do you have any idea what people are saying about you right now?

00:47:20.387 --> 00:47:24.202
That MD Jeon will end up as the head, and you'll be pushed out.

00:47:24.202 --> 00:47:25.731
Do you walk away with minimal damage,

00:47:25.731 --> 00:47:27.271
or do you get stripped of everything and tossed aside in disgrace?

00:47:27.271 --> 00:47:29.470
That's what everyone's buzzing about.

00:47:29.470 --> 00:47:32.160
So at a time like this,

00:47:32.160 --> 00:47:36.153
why can't you keep your own feelings in check and stop slipping up?

00:47:36.153 --> 00:47:38.730
I've been used to that kind of talk for ages.

00:47:38.730 --> 00:47:40.650
And I have regrets.

00:47:40.650 --> 00:47:42.660
About letting it sway me,

00:47:42.660 --> 00:47:45.303
about not being honest with my own feelings.

00:47:47.481 --> 00:47:48.785
So what then?

00:47:48.785 --> 00:47:50.446
What are you planning to do, following your heart?

00:47:50.446 --> 00:47:52.385
Are you going to die alongside Joo In Ah?

00:47:52.385 --> 00:47:54.805
After all, isn't she the woman you'd die with?

00:47:54.805 --> 00:47:57.906
The one getting emotional right now seems to be you, not me.

00:47:57.906 --> 00:47:59.677
So?

00:47:59.677 --> 00:48:02.888
Could you give it all up? For her sake?

00:48:02.888 --> 00:48:04.739
If that's what it takes.

00:48:26.537 --> 00:48:28.349
What's this?

00:48:34.297 --> 00:48:36.899
What made me buy this? Something I don't even use.

00:48:37.798 --> 00:48:41.860
From here on out, I'm becoming a real minimalist.

00:48:45.147 --> 00:48:46.893
Hey, just leave that be.

00:48:46.893 --> 00:48:48.677
You think there are no dishes in the U.S.?

00:48:48.677 --> 00:48:51.037
Take it for yourself.

00:48:51.037 --> 00:48:52.730
Anyway, looking at it now,

00:48:52.730 --> 00:48:54.943
it worked out that you moved into this place.

00:48:54.943 --> 00:48:59.085
If I had to scramble for a tenant while I'm off on the U.S. assignment...

00:49:02.022 --> 00:49:04.857
Hey, are you even listening?

00:49:04.857 --> 00:49:06.481
Ki Jun,

00:49:06.481 --> 00:49:09.284
did you know the Vice Chairman and Joo In Ah

00:49:09.284 --> 00:49:11.655
are heading to Jeju together next week?

00:49:13.523 --> 00:49:15.137
Yeah, I know.

00:49:15.137 --> 00:49:17.110
I checked the schedule.

00:49:17.110 --> 00:49:21.631
Jeju is where the two of them took a trip together.

00:49:21.631 --> 00:49:24.105
That's how precious the memory is to him,

00:49:24.105 --> 00:49:27.238
he's even held onto the plane tickets all this time.

00:49:29.478 --> 00:49:31.577
How modest of him.

00:49:31.577 --> 00:49:34.746
So even the rich go to Jeju for a couple's trip.

00:49:37.772 --> 00:49:40.794
Hey, I told you to keep that cup for yourself.

00:49:41.671 --> 00:49:44.051
Did you pack everything in?

00:49:44.051 --> 00:49:47.258
Hey, set this dish up there too.

00:49:53.710 --> 00:49:55.475
You okay?

00:50:01.022 --> 00:50:02.357
I'll go get it.

00:50:02.357 --> 00:50:04.401
The food we ordered must be here.

00:50:19.688 --> 00:50:21.356
What?

00:50:21.356 --> 00:50:23.169
Ki Jun.

00:50:46.360 --> 00:50:48.272
I'll head out for a bit.

00:50:48.272 --> 00:50:50.538
- We're out of bottled water. - Okay.

00:50:59.705 --> 00:51:00.777
What?

00:51:00.777 --> 00:51:02.057
Did I commit some kind of crime?

00:51:02.057 --> 00:51:03.097
I already explained the whole thing.

00:51:03.097 --> 00:51:05.312
I just lent her a room, that's all.

00:51:06.592 --> 00:51:08.691
Quit pinching me, will you?

00:51:11.205 --> 00:51:12.678
What kind of guy are you?

00:51:12.678 --> 00:51:14.442
You've got the woman who stayed by your sickbed,

00:51:14.442 --> 00:51:15.999
and a separate woman living with you on top of that?

00:51:15.999 --> 00:51:17.279
Who do you think you are? What gives you the right?

00:51:17.279 --> 00:51:19.518
I don't have the right.

00:51:19.518 --> 00:51:21.286
But here's the thing,

00:51:22.580 --> 00:51:25.065
she says she doesn't have feelings for me.

00:51:25.065 --> 00:51:26.984
What kind of nonsense are you talking?

00:51:26.984 --> 00:51:30.712
How would she act like that if she didn't have feelings, huh?

00:51:31.405 --> 00:51:32.451
I don't know. That's what she's saying.

00:51:32.451 --> 00:51:33.998
She says she's into another guy.

00:51:33.998 --> 00:51:35.967
So you'd better drop it too.

00:51:38.665 --> 00:51:39.731
You complete dimwit.

00:51:40.501 --> 00:51:42.981
How can you only go by what she's saying?

00:51:42.981 --> 00:51:45.002
Her behavior, expressions, that look in her eyes,

00:51:45.002 --> 00:51:47.217
those are what you should be watching!

00:51:47.217 --> 00:51:50.049
Hey, that look in her eyes while watching you sick? That one?

00:51:50.049 --> 00:51:51.845
Oh my gosh!

00:51:51.845 --> 00:51:53.722
This is so frustrating.

00:52:01.664 --> 00:52:03.497
It's a pleasure, by the way.

00:52:03.497 --> 00:52:05.705
Pleasure to meet you, too.

00:52:05.705 --> 00:52:08.875
- Nice to see you again. - Nice to see you again.

00:52:12.831 --> 00:52:15.123
I'm glad you like it.

00:52:15.123 --> 00:52:17.384
You should try this.

00:53:46.001 --> 00:53:49.690
<i>There's this weird thing where at crucial moments...</i>

00:53:50.294 --> 00:53:53.167
<i>I end up hiding what I really feel.</i>

00:54:16.487 --> 00:54:18.489
Where's the place in Jeju?

00:54:18.489 --> 00:54:19.147
<i>What?</i>

00:54:19.147 --> 00:54:21.386
I'm asking where in Jeju Joo In Ah is staying.

00:54:21.386 --> 00:54:22.626
Why are you asking,

00:54:22.626 --> 00:54:24.067
planning to chase her all the way out there?

00:54:24.067 --> 00:54:26.388
I asked you where, right now.

00:54:28.406 --> 00:54:30.684
Jeon Jae Yeol, Noh Ki Jun...

00:54:32.081 --> 00:54:34.729
both of you have totally lost it.

00:54:48.185 --> 00:54:49.898
The terms aren't half bad,

00:54:49.898 --> 00:54:52.064
though some fleshing out is needed.

00:54:52.064 --> 00:54:55.251
Still, I'd like the investment size to be a bit larger.

00:54:55.251 --> 00:54:57.239
That brings bigger risk along with it.

00:54:57.239 --> 00:54:59.199
For CPK, it's all just playing with money anyway.

00:54:59.199 --> 00:55:01.214
There's no soul in it.

00:55:07.956 --> 00:55:10.181
Coming back feels good.

00:55:13.881 --> 00:55:15.477
Jeju, I mean,

00:55:16.425 --> 00:55:20.141
it was our first and last trip together.

00:55:21.533 --> 00:55:24.758
We worked hard to line up the vacation and took the plunge,

00:55:25.472 --> 00:55:28.008
yet even back then, all we did was work like this.

00:55:31.956 --> 00:55:34.026
The board composition is what worries me most.

00:55:34.026 --> 00:55:35.610
In Ah.

00:55:40.747 --> 00:55:43.907
It seems you're having trouble focusing,

00:55:43.907 --> 00:55:46.493
so I'll review it on my own and report back to you separately.

00:55:46.493 --> 00:55:48.470
In Ah, hold on a second.

00:55:49.747 --> 00:55:51.518
For just a moment, the two of us,

00:55:53.039 --> 00:55:55.307
couldn't we be the way we used to?

00:56:02.039 --> 00:56:03.925
That's never going to happen,

00:56:05.158 --> 00:56:07.414
us going back to the way we used to be.

00:56:07.414 --> 00:56:09.628
Then why did you come back to Korea?

00:56:20.655 --> 00:56:21.987
Loyalty.

00:56:23.470 --> 00:56:26.081
That promise I made to stand by your side,

00:56:26.784 --> 00:56:28.577
this is the last bit of loyalty I owe to it.

00:56:28.577 --> 00:56:29.915
It's enough for me.

00:56:29.915 --> 00:56:32.984
It doesn't matter if it's loyalty or some other feeling,

00:56:34.150 --> 00:56:36.156
just stay right here by my side,

00:56:37.047 --> 00:56:38.516
that's all I need.

00:56:45.414 --> 00:56:47.492
I won't be doing even that anymore.

00:56:48.663 --> 00:56:50.883
Being held captive by that promise,

00:56:52.980 --> 00:56:55.214
I made a mistake I shouldn't have made.

00:56:57.580 --> 00:56:59.828
And I hurt someone,

00:57:02.114 --> 00:57:04.389
someone I should never have hurt.

00:57:08.039 --> 00:57:10.552
Are you talking about Mr. Noh?

00:57:21.997 --> 00:57:23.899
So that's why I'm telling you,

00:57:24.815 --> 00:57:27.492
I'm never coming back to you.

00:58:53.392 --> 00:58:56.395
It must be too late, right?

00:58:56.395 --> 00:58:58.701
For me to come to you.

00:59:04.486 --> 00:59:06.626
Joo In Ah!

00:59:29.612 --> 00:59:31.609
Joo In Ah!

00:59:48.197 --> 00:59:50.336
Noh Ki Jun...

01:00:05.678 --> 01:00:09.112
Why on earth did you check out so soon,

01:00:09.112 --> 01:00:11.733
after I went all the way out to that hotel...

01:01:56.071 --> 01:01:58.633
[Haemu Audit Team 3]

01:02:01.952 --> 01:02:06.313
[Joo In Ah is in an inappropriate relationship with a coworker]

01:02:07.958 --> 01:02:10.445
[Joo In Ah is in an inappropriate relationship with a coworker]

01:02:18.927 --> 01:02:22.875
[Send]

01:02:54.330 --> 01:02:56.051
<i>By the way, something's been bothering me,</i>

01:02:56.051 --> 01:02:59.435
<i>how obvious my feelings for you might be at work.</i>

01:03:00.177 --> 01:03:01.831
<i>Clear your whole weekend.</i>

01:03:01.831 --> 01:03:03.471
<i>I've booked a pool villa in Sokcho.</i>

01:03:03.471 --> 01:03:06.099
<i>Then you should go to Mr. Min's club event this weekend.</i>

01:03:06.099 --> 01:03:06.901
<i>What?</i>

01:03:06.901 --> 01:03:08.685
<i>You said you'd be on fire once we started dating,</i>

01:03:08.685 --> 01:03:10.341
<i>but you're firing work at me like flames instead.</i>

01:03:10.341 --> 01:03:13.340
<i>Want to stay for some ramyeon?</i>

01:03:13.340 --> 01:03:15.021
<i>Must be fun for you, isn't it,</i>

01:03:15.021 --> 01:03:16.363
<i>stuck between two men?</i>

01:03:16.363 --> 01:03:17.627
<i>I'm getting a divorce.</i>

01:03:17.627 --> 01:03:19.616
<i>I have regrets about everything.</i>

01:03:19.616 --> 01:03:21.545
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

